Butter Pecan Cornbread
  --wick'd confections
  
Bread:
 1 c (120g) ap flour
 1 c (120g) cornmeal
 ⅓ c (67g) granulated sugar
 ⅓ c (67g) brown sugar
 2 tsp (8g) baking powder
 1 tsp (5g) kosher salt
 1 large egg
 1 tsp (5ml) vanilla 
 ½ c (120ml) buttermilk
 ½ c (120ml) butter pecan creamer
 4 tbsp (56g) butter, melted
 4 tbsp (60ml) oil
 1 c (120g) pecan pieces
 ¼ c (43g)  toffee bits (optional)
 10 shortbread cookies, crushed
 2 tbsp (16g) cookie-style pecans for topping

Preheat the oven to 375F (190C). Grease a 9x9" baking pan or line with parchment paper. In a large bowl, mix flour, cornmeal, granulated sugar, brown sugar, baking powder, and salt. In a separate bowl, whisk together the egg, vanilla extract, buttermilk, butter pecan creamer, melted butter, and oil until smooth. Pour the wet ingredients into the dry ingredients, stirring until just combined. Gently fold in the pecan pieces, toffee bits and crushed shortbread cookies. Pour the batter into the prepared baking pan and sprinkle the cookie-style pecans on top. Bake for 25-30 min, or until a toothpick inserted into the center comes out clean. Allow to cool slightly before slicing. Enjoy this cornbread warm or at room temperature!


Brown Sugar Bourbon Glaze:
3 tbsp (42g) butter
Pinch of salt
3 tbsp (45ml) bourbon
2 tbsp (24g) brown sugar
1 tbsp (15ml) honey

In a small saucepan, melt the butter over medium heat. Stir in the salt, bourbon, brown sugar, and honey. Continue cooking, stirring occasionally, until the sugar dissolves and the glaze thickens slightly, ~3-4 min. Remove from heat and let cool slightly before using. This glaze is perfect for drizzling over grilled meats, roasted vegetables, or even desserts like cakes and ice cream!


Whipped Pecan Praline Butter:
1 c (226g) unsalted butter, softened
½ c (60g) powdered sugar
⅓ c (80ml) honey
2 tbsp (30ml) maple syrup
1 tsp (5ml) vanilla extract
½ tsp (1g) cinnamon
⅛ tsp (0.5g) salt
¼ c (30g) pecan cookie pieces

In a large mixing bowl, beat the softened butter until smooth and creamy. Gradually add powdered sugar, honey, and maple syrup, beating until fluffy and fully combined. Mix in vanilla extract, cinnamon, and salt. Gently fold in the pecan cookie pieces until evenly distributed. Transfer to a serving bowl or storage container and refrigerate for 1 hr to set. Enjoy this butter spread on warm toast, pancakes, or waffles!
